# `{{ lab_name }}` — Agent Operating Guide

You are working inside a trestle-scaffolded open lakehouse lab. This document
tells you (an AI coding agent) how to extend the lab without breaking the
**Databricks parity** the stack provides.

## The single most important rule

**Code that uses MLflow, Unity Catalog, Delta, or any Databricks REST API must
not hardcode hostnames or auth.** Read these env vars instead:

| Variable | What it points to locally | Where it comes from on Databricks |
|----------|--------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| `DATABRICKS_HOST` | `http://localhost:$ENVOY_PORT` (Envoy) | Injected by Databricks Apps |
| `DATABRICKS_TOKEN` | Synthetic local token | OBO header `X-Forwarded-Access-Token` |
| `MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI` | `http://localhost:$ENVOY_PORT` (Envoy rewrites `/api/2.0/mlflow/*`) | `https://<workspace>` |
| `AWS_*` / `MLFLOW_S3_ENDPOINT_URL` | SeaweedFS at `:$SEAWEEDFS_S3_PORT` | The workspace's storage credentials |

Same code, different environment values. Always set these from `os.environ`,
never inline.

