## How to extend the stack

When you need a new backing service (Redis, OpenSearch, Trino, Kafka, …):

1. Add a compose fragment under `docker/compose/<service>.yaml`.
2. Add a corresponding entry to `compose.yaml` under `include:`.
3. (Optional) Add an Envoy route in `docker/envoy/envoy.yaml` if the service
   should be reachable over the unified `localhost:$ENVOY_PORT` endpoint.
4. (Optional) Append env vars to `.env.example`.

If you find yourself doing this often, factor the service into a new trestle
shared component (see the trestle README); that gives you the same composition
in any future lab.

